text: Ðys synd þa þing þe <man> gedon hæfþ to ðornige, ærest man bohte twa ðusend hæringes myd xl penegun & þonne to beansæde xl penega, fif oran Æþelferþe æt Niwantune æt hys men, twegen oran <wæron> to scipe & to <nettum> to Fearresheafde, & wyþ þrim gegrindum æt þiutforda man sealde <oran> & xii penegas & anne wifman v orena wyrþe to Stangrunde & iii <egeðan> <þreora> orena wyrþe, an man sealde to Niwantune, oþer to Geaceslea, þridde to Stangrunde, & xv penegas wyþ <beansæde> to Geaceslea, & to oþrum scipe to Witlesmere & wið nettum <peniga>, & nigon <oran> wið anum mæder werde to Huntandune.
An scip twegra orena wyrþ <man> sealde fram Elig to Witlesige.
Þæt is þonne ealles feorðe healf pund butun þrittigun penega.
Þonne dyde man æfter ðæm hundeahtatig swyna & þone swan fram <Middeltune>.
Þa geeahtade man þa <swin> to oðran healfan punde & þone swan to healfan punde.
& xii wænas myd hundeahtigum penegun, & iiii scipa myd eahta oran ælc myd ii oran an <man> dyde to Niwantune, oþer to Geaceslea, þridde to Stangrunde, feorðe to Witlesmere.
& <man> sealde Ælfnoþe tyn mancusas goldes to mylenoxan to Huntadune & Ælfsige munuce on fif mancesun <goldes> & Swetan an pund to mylenoxan to Geaceslea & to x <pund>.
& butan þæm se abbud <sealde> Ælfsige munuce to fyrþrunge to þorniges are <mancusa> goldes.
& v orena <wæron> to þrym mylnun to isene twegra orena wyrþ to Huntandune, twegra to Geaceslea & anes to Stangrunde.
Þæt is þonne ealles geseald of Elig to ðornige butun hyra scrudfeo þe on golde & on <seolfre> syxtena punda wyrþ butun feowertigum penegun.
Þæs þe <asme> & marun.
Þonne siþþan ofer þa xvi pund man sealde fram Hæþfelda XXX ealdra swyna ælce to vi pænegum <ofer>.
& man sealde wyþ þan æt þæm smyþe fif mancusas gold & <dware>.
& man <sealde> Cynesiges swystor mylen Bluntesham <gehht>.
& ane dægan to Lindune to þiuwan.
& butan þisum eallum þæt <heron> gewriten is ma <sealde> ærest se bisceop þriu pund to Geaceslea to fyrþrunge & þa man sealde þriu punda wyrþ goldes.
Þa nam man þærof an pund to scrude, oþer to Fearresheafde to dycynge, þæt þridde to fyrþrunge to Geaceslea.
& man sealde Ælfsige munece lx <mancusas> & fif pænega <gerihta> to Geaceslea to fyrþrunga.
Nenien <briht>.
Æt byryg xlvii ealdra swina & cc geongra butun ðrim.
Æt Strætham xx sugena <æt>.
Xx sugena & L hogga.
Æt Horningesige xviii <ealde> swyn & xl hogga.
<Æt> & xliiii hogga.
Æt Hafucestune xxx ealdra swyna & c hogga butun i.
Æt Meldeburnan xxii sugena, of þære heorde þe Alfwold heold æt Hæðfelda xii sige & lxxxii <geongra> swina & Ælfnoð of þære oþre heorde xiii sige & lx hogga.
Of þæm feo þe æþelflæd sealde man sealde to <sceapum> to Bromdune lx penega & lx <penega>.
Iii oran Leofrice æt Strætham æt his corne x penega ufan æt <his>.
& x penega þæm <sceaphyrde>, healf pund þæm abbot, healf pund Byryhtmære & Wulfrice.
& <oran> æt i wife æt Strætham & æt <twam> werum þærto & iii mancusas hyringmannum.
Þa man betæhte Ælfnoðe þone folgað æt Hæðfelda þa wæs þær xl oxana, <þrydde> healf hund sceapa, xlvii gata & xv cealfra, cc <swina> butun x, xliii flicca.
Þis is þæs fænnes hyre æt Fordham & æt Hyllingyge <þe> <get> Eadgares sunu & æt Wulfsie, þæt sent iiii ðusend.

Of ðæm <east> fenne ii ðusend, <pole> xx snasa, of <tynadwere> & of forwerde x <snasa>, of soþan ea & xx <snasa>, of ladwere i þusend, of burhwere <ðusend>, of <mudecanwere> <wewer> & of ðæm <þusend>, of <sceld> xiiii snasa, of were oðer healf, of <wratwere> ii ðusend, of <bulingge> snasa, of batlin <ðusend>, of brade sealde xx snasa, of Wulfgaringwere x snasa, of <heamuces>, of norþwere xx <snasa>, of Osgoding i ðusend, of were ii ðusend, of i <ðusend>.
Þis synd xxvi ðusend & xi sticcan.
